{"type": "edit", "field": "description", "label": "Description", "before": "To receive free diapers you must:\\nHave a child 2 years and younger who resides with you (including expecting moms with other children, a doctor's note as proof of pregnancy is required)\\nLive in the New York City area\\nReceive WIC and/or SNAP (food stamps)\\nBring Photo ID, Proof of address (no more than 90 days old old-electricity bill/light bill/doctor's letter/note with client\u2019s name and address), Birth certificate(s) for baby or hospital discharge papers for newborn Food Stamps/SNAP proof, WIC Proof-WIC app on a cellphone or WIC card with a letter/note from WIC office\\nFood stamps proof or recent budget letter\\nShopping cart and/or bags \\nExpectant Moms Program\\n", "after": "To receive free diapers you must:\\n  \u2014 Have a child 2 years and younger who resides with you (including expecting moms with other children, a doctor's note as proof of pregnancy is required)\\nLive in the New York City area\\nBring:\\n  \u2014 Photo ID, Proof of address (no more than 90 days old old-electricity bill/light bill/doctor's letter/note with client's name and address), \\n  \u2014 Birth certificate(s) for baby or hospital discharge papers for newborn \\n  \u2014 Food Stamps/SNAP proof or recent budget letter, \\n  \u2014 WIC app on a cellphone or WIC card with a letter/note from the WIC office, \\n  \u2014 Shopping cart, and/or bags \\n", "note": "Updated Description", "summary": "Updated Description", "ts": "2024-08-26T20:29:10Z", "userName": "doobneek", "pagePath": "/team/location/f46f0b75-4beb-47b1-a3b2-dd6fbc86c56b/services/8b3550e2-c9d3-4b2a-8a5f-b898f39561b0/description", "locationId": "f46f0b75-4beb-47b1-a3b2-dd6fbc86c56b", "serviceId": "8b3550e2-c9d3-4b2a-8a5f-b898f39561b0", "resourceTable": "services", "action": "update", "copyedit": false}

/locationNotes/%2Fteam%2Flocation%2F8b29: {"type": "edit", "field": "description", "label": "Description", "before": "CIDNY has three offices across NYC. It can serve NYC residents with disabilities regardless of immigration status (some reimbursement and benefit programs are tied to SSDI and are unavailable to some non-citizens). Parental consent is required for underage participants. Many programs are tied to employment, so a valid work permit or US citizenship/residency is required. \\nServices Include* and are available in many languages with accommodation for the deaf, blind, and people with other challenges. All facilities are ADA-compliant:\\n\u2022 Information and referral, nutritional outreach, job readiness, peer support, and independent living (for example, during readjustment after returning home from a nursing facility)\\n\u2022 Free training, reasonable accommodation, transportation expense reimbursement, affordable housing, and benefits (compensated through Social Security only for people with a qualified disability, income, and immigration status)\\n*People convicted of a sex crime are not served.", "after": "CIDNY has three offices across NYC. It can serve NYC residents with disabilities regardless of immigration status (some reimbursement and benefit programs are tied to SSDI and are unavailable to some non-citizens).
